title: Income VS Degree
text:
This is a Quarto website.

Load necessary libraries
library(tidyverse) #| message: false library(lubridate)


Load the CSV file into R
data <- read.csv(“Users/anshkare/Downloads/archive (3).zip/adult.csv”)


Create the grouped bar plot
ggplot(data, aes(x = education, fill = income)) + geom_bar(position = “dodge”) + labs(title = “Income Levels by Education”, x = “Education Level”, y = “Count”) + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
